results.abstract: US astronaut Capt C Conrad Jr says Skylab astronauts have rescue plan in case of emergency; orbiting laboratory will carry med equip for minor surgery, and rescue spacecraft will be on hand for emergencies or serious illnesses
results.snippet: America's Skylab astronauts this spring will be the first men to go into space with a chance of rescue if things go wrong, a veteran astronaut, Capt. Charles Conrad Jr., said this week.
results.lead_paragraph: America's Skylab astronauts this spring will be the first men to go into space with a chance of rescue if things go wrong, a veteran astronaut, Capt. Charles Conrad Jr., said this week.

headline.main: Montclair Greets P. O. W. With a Look Back at 1950; Sprinkling of Uniforms

results.snippet: With Sousa marches, highschool cheers and the harmonies of a barbershop chorus, Montclair today welcomed a native son, Comdr. Robert B. Doremus, back after seven and a half years as a prisoner of war.

results.abstract: Prof K Bushuyev, Soviet tech dir of '75 joint US-USSR space venture, discloses on Mar 19 that Amer flight controllers will be allowed to work at consoles of Soviet space center 'on the basis of tech necessity,' news conf, Houston; during joint mission Soviet flight controllers will also be working in Amer control center at Houston; Amer controllers probably will not be admitted to Soviet launching sites at Baikonur

headline.main: Americans to Be at Soviet Consoles in Space Mission; Cooperation Hailed

results.snippet: Soviet space officials have agreed that, for the 1975 joint mission between American and Soviet astronauts, American flight controllers will be allowed at the consoles of the Soviet control center "on the basis of technical necessity."
results.lead_paragraph: Soviet space officials have agreed that, for the 1975 joint mission between American and Soviet astronauts, American flight controllers will be allowed at the consoles of the Soviet control center "on the basis of technical necessity."
